<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-11-18T04:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-11-18T04:00:00-05:00" n="668" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d668">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">893.51/3066: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Crane</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-11-18T17:00:00+08:00"><hi rend="italic">November
                                            18, 1920—5 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received November
                                    18—2:40 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>388. Your 331, November 12, 7 p.m. Minister of Finance informally
                                advises Legation payment not made owing to lack of funds. He hopes
                                to remit to Chicago interest money end of this month and has so
                                advised. Am writing Minister of Finance in the sense of Department’s
                                telegram leaving out reference to consortium.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Crane</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>